---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const updated = '2026-07-13';
---

<BaseLayout title="Cookie Policy" description="How VisaLang uses analytics, preference cookies, and third-party embeds while keeping language-exam route guidance privacy-conscious." noindex={true}>
  <main class="page-shell">
    <article class="guide-article narrow-page">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p class="guide-summary">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <h2>What are cookies</h2>
        <p>Cookies are small text files stored in your browser. VisaLang uses them sparingly.</p>

        <h2>Cookies and local storage we use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Advertising and consent:</strong> Google AdSense and the related consent message may use cookies or local storage for advertising, consent and measurement where permitted by your choices and applicable requirements.</li>
          <li><strong>Tool progress:</strong> route and tool interfaces may use browser local storage to keep progress on your device. This information is not sent to VisaLang by that storage alone.</li>
          <li><strong>Future analytics:</strong> Plausible Analytics is not enabled on the current Astro site. If it is enabled, Plausible’s standard service is configured without analytics cookies or persistent identifiers.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Third-party social tracking</h2>
        <p>We do not use third-party social-media tracking cookies. Third-party sites you visit from VisaLang, including official sources and advertising destinations, apply their own policies.</p>

        <h2>Managing cookies</h2>
        <p>Where the European consent message is shown, use it to accept, reject, or manage advertising choices. You can also clear or block cookies and local storage in your browser settings. Doing so may affect advertising choices or remove saved tool progress.</p>

        <h2>Third-party embeds</h2>
        <p>If we embed official videos or resources from external providers, those providers may set their own cookies.</p>

        <h2>Questions or changes</h2>
        <p>For privacy questions, use our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>. We update this page when our cookie, consent, analytics, or advertising approach changes.</p>

        <p class="compliance-line">See also our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
